text: Padasjoki is a municipality in Päijänne Tavastia, Finland. About 3,319 people lived there as of 31 May 2013. Nearby municipalities include Asikkala, Hämeenlinna, Kangasala, Kuhmoinen, Pälkäne and Sysmä. ==History== People lived in the area of Padasjoki during the Stone Age. There is hill fort around the town. ==Other websites== * Community website Category:Municipalities of Päijät-Häme
